cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is about a new dataset for remote sensing image understanding using deep learning models. The paper focuses on the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for multi-label classification of Sentinel-2 multispectral images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of DL models for better learning and describing the complex spatial and spectral information content of the Sentinel-2 images, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of an alternative class-nomenclature to allow DL models for better learning, which could also suggest that it belongs to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the use of multi-label classification, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
